summary: do you think the chances of s4 have increased, decreased, or stayed about the same lately? back in early s3 i was like yeah am...
question: do you think the chances of s4 have increased, decreased, or stayed about the same lately? back in early s3 i was like yeah am is donezo lol but now...i feel like s4 has a chance? idk i don't get the impression that disney have made a final decision or that perhaps they thought they had, but now they're hesitating/reconsidering.
answer:
i don’t think our actual chances have changed all that much - because we never knew what are chances were to begin with. we don’t know what goes on behind the scenes, we can only theorize and speculate.

i think our hope for renewal has changed over time. i think that when season 3 started, renewal wasn’t really on most people’s minds. but by the time of the hiatus after the new girls (and the wrapping of filming for season 3 in december) - people started to panic a little bit, realizing that this season could be our last. based on posts from the cast and the westmoreland situation, a lot of people became hopeless, thinking that we were definitely done. but then after one in a minyan aired, i think it started to feel like anything was possible - and that helped us find the drive to hope for renewal, even if it may not happen. 

i don’t think disney has made their final decision yet, but i don’t know what our chances are. i never did. nobody does. as long as the season 3 finale is satisfying, i’m still going to be content with three seasons if that’s all we get. but it doesn’t hurt to campaign and try to get renewed. it doesn’t matter what our chances are because supporting the show and campaigning for renewal isn’t just about getting a season 4 - but also a way of showing terri, the cast, and the crew how much we care about what they’ve done. that’s just as much a part of why i’m doing the project and promoting the show as the chance of renewal is.
